The paper discusses the use of Information Centric Networking (ICN) for distributed spatial databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of routing-by-name, in-network caching, and data-centric security, which are all related to networking (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the design choices that lead to performance suitable for real-world applications, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of secure multi-tenancy, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
